{
  "ComponentName": "Mk82 Railgun",
  "LongDescription": "The Alliance Mk8X Railgun provides a heavy warship with long-range direct-fire offensive ability, intended to pressure targets caught out in open space and foregoing cover. Alliance railguns typically lack the explosive power of their favored cannon weapons but make up for it with precision fire that can trigger fires and other debilitating effects on targets.\n\nThis model of the 8X is equipped with an additional rail at the cost of recharge time and power draw. Fires 300mm Magnetic rounds.",
  "FlavorText": "I remember reading a report about an \"attempt\" to make a tri-railed battery but it turns out that the coils were so close to each other by that point that it would send the shells forward and then launch them back into the turret at Mach 8, completely blowing out the back because of the reversing frequencies.\n\nNaval Office wasn't happy, neither was the War Office when they got issued the field tests during the Deshima Blitz and lost a whole battery, a lot of expletives and a busted jaw on a Naval Office guy, that part's a little spotty.\n\n- T. Meadows, LT",
